	   <a name=9828835864404></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9828835864404><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>RE: dex/agility or str?</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Feb 22nd 6:13 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I can't BELIEVE what i'm reading.&nbsp;&nbsp;STAMINA??<br>No No No No No!<br><br>Stamina will increase the length of time you can swing a stick....but let's think about this for in the LONG term.  After all, we are playing these monks so that "one" day they'll be in the higher lvls, correct?  At the higher lvls, your fists will do WAY more dmg than any weapon you can put in your hands, you have NO need to ever pick up a weapon.  (of course, if you find one helpful in the earlier levels, then by all means, use one)  There is no need to buff up Dexterity just so your skills will increase...as long as your DEX is in the 80-90 range, your skills will max out before you reach the next lvl just from fighting.  Which leaves of course, agility.....and strength. This is more of a personal choice....do you want to avoid more damage, or do more damage?  I find a high agility to be EXTREMELY useful in the later levels....in the 45-60 range...you can have an AC over 100 points higher than anybody you run across.  Agility might not make a big AC difference in the beginning.....but later on.....it pays off.  So, my recommendation, put everything into Agility.  <br><br><br>Lvl 59 Master Torvonnilous<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
